<div id="review_3409255453" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3409255453" />
    <a title="Kiran Bhat" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81560301-kiran-bhat"><img alt="Kiran Bhat" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1525335374p2/81560301.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3409255453?book_show_action=true">Jun 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kiran Bhat" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kiran Bhat" href="/user/show/81560301-kiran-bhat">Kiran Bhat</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3409255453" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16693050306518461814">One of the most powerful novels of the 20th century. Mahfouz takes Cairo and makes it his own the way Balzac commands Paris. His depictions of inter-generational conflict and misunderstanding are some of the best I have seen portrayed yet in literature. His translated writing is also not particularly difficult to get into, and so his work is easy to recommend to someone who wants to read something linguistically simple, yet emotionally complex.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


