<span id="freeTextContainer9767098906836984670">This 1,313-page novel by Naguib Mafouz who received the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1988 is seemingly formidable but in fact it is highly readable since the team of four scholars have translated so beautifully that we readers can read on and on without any regrets due to our ignorance of its Arabian original version. </span>

