<div id="review_165296601" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/165296601" />
    <a title="Chris Moriarty" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5315793-chris-moriarty"><img alt="Chris Moriarty" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442450576p2/5315793.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/165296601?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chris Moriarty" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chris Moriarty" href="/user/show/5315793-chris-moriarty">Chris Moriarty</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer165296601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12512738853758715417">Forget about the Nobel Prize for a minute. This is not stuffy pretentious Capital L Literature. It&apos;s a potboiler family saga in the grand 19th century tradition. If you have ever complained that Trollope didn&apos;t write ENOUGH, then Naguib Mahfouz is your new best friend.<br/><br/>Oh ... And there&apos;s poignant irony, proustian characters, profound insights into human nature, the history of modern Egypt all wrapped up into one soaringly poetic masterpiece .... Yeah. Fine. Whatever. <br/><br/>The main point is that you&apos;d </span>
  <span id="freeText12512738853758715417" style="display:none">Forget about the Nobel Prize for a minute. This is not stuffy pretentious Capital L Literature. It's a potboiler family saga in the grand 19th century tradition. If you have ever complained that Trollope didn't write ENOUGH, then Naguib Mahfouz is your new best friend.<br /><br />Oh ... And there's poignant irony, proustian characters, profound insights into human nature, the history of modern Egypt all wrapped up into one soaringly poetic masterpiece .... Yeah. Fine. Whatever. <br /><br />The main point is that you'd better make sure to buy all three volumes in the trilogy up front, because once you crack page one you are not coming up for air until it's done, done, done. These books will take control of your life and make you forget to eat, sleep or breathe until you're finished with them. They really truly are that good. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12512738853758715417" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


